TITLE: Handling zp-body-removed Header in Zuplo Custom Policy
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code snippet demonstrates a custom policy for Zuplo that checks for the zp-body-removed header and returns a bad request response if a body was removed from a GET or HEAD request. It uses Zuplo's runtime library and the HttpProblems utility for generating the response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zuplo/docs/blob/main/docs/articles/zp-body-removed.md#2025-04-08_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { HttpProblems, ZuploContext, ZuploRequest } from "@zuplo/runtime";

export default async function (request: ZuploRequest, context: ZuploContext) {
  const bodyRemoved = request.headers.get("zp-body-removed");

  if (bodyRemoved) {
    return HttpProblems.badRequest(request, context, {
      detail: `GET or HEAD requests can't have a body.`,
    });
  }

  return request;
}
```

