TITLE: Implementing Sign Out Route Handler with Supabase in Next.js
DESCRIPTION: This code implements a Next.js route handler for user sign-out functionality. It uses Supabase authentication to sign out the current user and redirects them to either a specified redirect_uri or the login page. The handler extracts the redirect URI from the query parameters and uses the Supabase client to manage the authentication state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zuplo/docs/blob/main/docs/articles/dev-portal-supabase-auth.md#2025-04-08_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const requestUrl = new URL(request.url);
  // The Developer Portal will send a `redirect_uri` query parameter to this
  // route. This is the URL that the user should be redirected to after signing
  // out.
  const redirectUri = requestUrl.searchParams.get("redirect_uri");
  const supabase = createRouteHandlerClient({ cookies });

  await supabase.auth.signOut();

  return NextResponse.redirect(redirectUri ?? `${requestUrl.origin}/login`, {
    status: 301,
  });
}
```

