TITLE: Configuring GitHub Actions Workflow for Zuplo Testing
DESCRIPTION: GitHub Actions workflow configuration that runs tests after a successful Zuplo deployment. This workflow uses the deployment_status event to trigger testing and passes the environment URL to the test commands for validating the deployed API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zuplo/docs/blob/main/docs/articles/testing.md#2025-04-08_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
name: Main
on: [deployment_status]

jobs:
  test:
    name: Test API Gateway
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Use Node.js
        uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version-file: ".nvmrc"

      - name: Run Tests
        # Useful properties 'environment', 'state', and 'environment_url'
        run:
          API_URL=${{ toJson(github.event.deployment_status.environment_url) }}
          npx zuplo test --endpoint $API_URL
```

